I cannot reproduce your bug.
Would you mind trying the following command: Assuming you have installed tomoe:
wget http://download.fedoraproject.org/pub/fedora/linux/updates/23/x86_64/t/tomoe-gtk-0.6.0-24.fc23.x86_64.rpm
Make sure the size is: 62078 Md5 checksum: 39e57cb3a73cfcd3738922f4660de71a
And then:
sudo rpm -ivh tomoe-gtk-0.6.0-24.fc23.x86_64.rpm
If that works, that means some thing wrong with your repos or cache. You may run "dnf clean all" to clean it, and/or choose more reliable repo.
If that does work, I am out of tricks.

Is there any chance that a new file in f23 is trying to use a file that was the wrong type in a previous version (like a regular file instead of a directory) or something really weird like that - or something that would normally be created by some other tomoe sort of file that might not yet be created? It's got to be something like that since cpio is failing if it works for you. If the contents are correct based on above sums then cpio must not be able to extract due to other file. F22 was installed fine by something though so it has to be some different file or possibly user creation from before the moving of the UIDs?

Some more tricks:
Try: rpm -qpl tomoe-gtk-0.6.0-24.fc23.x86_64.rpm
If that does not work, try:
rpm2cpio tomoe-gtk-0.6.0-24.fc23.x86_64.rpm| cpio -dtv
And
lsb_release -a
If above does not work, try fixing your partition.

All right.
The problem is that ./usr/share/locale/ja.po is a file in fedora 22 (and I'm pretty sure in other releases as well) and not a directory, so when it tries to create ./usr/share/locale/ja.po/LC_MESSAGES/tomoe-gtk.mo it fails.
That isn't a surprise since I'm pretty sure it should be /usr/share/locale/ja/LC_MESSAGES/tomoe-gtk.mo and not ja.po

> That isn't a surprise since I'm pretty sure it should be > /usr/share/locale/ja/LC_MESSAGES/tomoe-gtk.mo and not ja.po
Well spot! We are getting somewhere. But in that cases, the error message will more likely to be file conflict instead of cpio error.
Fix is on the way.
